 Nigeria Immigration Service  The NIS Comptroller in the state, Mr. Ajisafe Joshua Olusola, disclosed this during a press briefing yesterday. Olusola identified the suspects as Omoseyin Solomon, 43, and Omoniyi Olowoporoku, 32, all males. He said they were arrested separately at Mazanya and Daura Patrol Border Base between January 17, and 19, 2019. He said one of the suspected human traffickers, Solomon, claimed to be husband to his victim, Akinbayo Ashobi, a woman known to also be a human trafficker. He, however, said that the suspects would be handed over to the service headquarters for further investigations and necessary actions. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .